  h2.inline-block Tooltips
  a.text-underline.text-grey.text-smaller.inline-block(href="https://github.com/amelia-lewis/wgsn-styleguide/blob/master/public/css/_tooltips.sass" target="_blank") View on Github
  
  p Tooltips appear on hover. They are intended for non-vital information about a given element.
  p A tooltip requires that the element has a 
    code data-tooltip
    |  attribute containing the tooltip content. By default, the tooltip appears above the element.

  .card
    .block-md.text-center
      p.has-tooltip(data-tooltip="I'm a tooltip") Hover me.

  include:markdown tooltips-1.md

  p There are a number of modifiers available to change the direction and behaviour of the tooltip:

  .card  
    .block-md.text-center
      p.has-tooltip.tooltip-right(data-tooltip="I'm a tooltip") This one will appear to the right.

    .block-md.text-center
      p.has-tooltip.tooltip-down(data-tooltip="I'm a tooltip") This one will appear underneath.

    .block-md.text-center
      p.has-tooltip.tooltip-left(data-tooltip="I'm a tooltip") This one will appear to the left.

